"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657017","HM Treasury","false","2016-12-20","<p>I refer the Hon. Member to the oral statement on the Corporate Governance Green Paper of 29 November 2016, Official Report, Column 1408.</p><p> </p><p>The green paper can be found as follows: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/news/government-launches-review-of-corporate-governance" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/news/government-launches-review-of-corporate-governance</a></p><p> </p>","Brighton, Kemptown","Simon Kirby",,"2016-12-20T14:10:02.017Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657017/answer","Biography information for Simon Kirby","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657017/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657017/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-12-12","Treasury: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what plans his Department has to include worker representation on its departmental board.","false","Biography information for Jake Berry","Rossendale and Darwen","Jake Berry","57020"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657018","HM Treasury","false","2016-12-19","<p>The Treasury does not publish the percentage pay gap in earnings.</p><p> </p><p>However, information about current HM Treasury pay multiples is on page 67 in the Annual Report and Accounts 2015-2016 which can be found here: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/533615/annual_report_and_accounts_2016_-_web.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/533615/annual_report_and_accounts_2016_-_web.pdf</a></p>","Brighton, Kemptown","Simon Kirby","57042","2016-12-19T12:33:50.483Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657018/answer","Biography information for Simon Kirby","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657018/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657018/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-12-12","Treasury: Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what the percentage gap in earnings is between the highest-paid and lowest-paid full-time employee in his Department.","false","Biography information for Jake Berry","Rossendale and Darwen","Jake Berry","56998"
