"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657042","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-12-16","<p>The flight sciences test programme is making good progress and the F-35B programme remains on track to deliver initial operating capability for the UK by the end of 2018.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2016-12-16T13:02:26.33Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657042/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657042/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657042/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-12-12","Joint Strike Fighter Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what assessment he has made of the F35B Lightning II's progress in flight sciences testing in 2016.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","57051"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657043","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-12-16","<p>Block 3F is the capability standard that the UK will use to declare initial operating capability for the UK F-35B. This remains on schedule for the end of 2018.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2016-12-16T13:02:02.44Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657043/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657043/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657043/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-12-12","Joint Strike Fighter Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what assessment he has made of the likelihood that the F35B Lightning II will achieve full Block 3F combat capability within the current timetable.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","57052"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657044","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-12-15","<p>The Ministry of Defence published the 2016 Armed Forces Covenant Annual Report today. This will help demonstrate that while more remains to be done this Nation is honouring its pledge to the Armed Forces Community past and present; this includes tangible progress made and support offered by Departments of State, Local Authorities, the Devolved Administrations, Businesses, Charities and society as a whole.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2016-12-15T16:14:14.753Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657044/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657044/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657044/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-12-12","Armed Forces Covenant","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, when his Department plans to publish its annual report on the Armed Forces Covenant.","false","Biography information for Anne-Marie Trevelyan","Berwick-upon-Tweed","Mrs Anne-Marie Trevelyan","57063"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657045","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-12-16","<p>Testing for Autonomous Logistics Information System version 2.0.2 is expected to be complete by February 2017.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2016-12-16T13:03:37.89Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657045/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657045/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657045/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-12-12","Joint Strike Fighter Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, when his Department expects testing on the Autonomous Logistics Information System version 2.0.2 for the F35B Lightning II to be completed.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","57049"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657046","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-12-16","<p>Testing and certification of the F-35B Lightning's gun pod, for use on UK aircraft, is expected to be completed as part of the next Block upgrade programme, Block 4.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2016-12-16T13:06:01.547Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657046/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657046/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657046/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-12-12","Joint Strike Fighter Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, when his Department expects testing on the F35B Lightning II's gun pod to be completed.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","57050"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657047","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-12-15","<p>The UK has taken delivery of seven F-35B aircraft and there are a further seven on order. The Strategic Defence and Security Review 2015 set out the UK's intent to have two front line operations F-35 squadrons by the end of 2023 and plan to buy 138 aircraft over the life of the programme. The year by year buy profile is not published, as it can undermine our commercial position during the aircraft procurement process.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2016-12-15T16:13:42.247Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657047/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657047/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657047/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-12-12","Joint Strike Fighter Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many F35 Lightning II fighters have been purchased to date; and how many such fighters his Department plans to purchase in each year until 2023.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","57074"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657048","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-12-15","<p>Defence has over 4,000 military personnel that have had some training in driving coaches and/or buses although driving is not necessarily their primary role. Of which, approximately 250 military personnel have been trained in driving coaches/buses in the last 12 months. Defence has no military personnel trained to drive a train.</p><p>Military operations in the UK are placed under the overarching title of Military Aid to the Civil Authorities (MACA), which is only in support of, and at the request of, the lead Government Department. Defence continues to work closely with the Department for Transport (and other Government Departments) to determine areas where military support within the UK is necessary, achievable, and permitted.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning","56946","2016-12-15T16:08:06.087Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657048/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657048/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657048/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-12-12","Armed Forces: Railways","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many military personnel who are able to drive (a) trains, (b) coaches and (c) buses could potentially be deployed in the event of industrial action on the rail network.","false","Biography information for Tim Loughton","East Worthing and Shoreham","Tim Loughton","56945"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657049","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-12-15","<p>Defence has over 4,000 military personnel that have had some training in driving coaches and/or buses although driving is not necessarily their primary role. Of which, approximately 250 military personnel have been trained in driving coaches/buses in the last 12 months. Defence has no military personnel trained to drive a train.</p><p>Military operations in the UK are placed under the overarching title of Military Aid to the Civil Authorities (MACA), which is only in support of, and at the request of, the lead Government Department. Defence continues to work closely with the Department for Transport (and other Government Departments) to determine areas where military support within the UK is necessary, achievable, and permitted.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning","56945","2016-12-15T16:08:06.037Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657049/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657049/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657049/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-12-12","Armed Forces: Driving","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many military personnel are trained to drive (a) buses, (b) trains and (c) coaches.","false","Biography information for Tim Loughton","East Worthing and Shoreham","Tim Loughton","56946"
