"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657167","Department of Health","false","2016-12-15","<p>The Department does not make comparative assessment of whether care providers are compliant with the national minimum wage and the business failure of such providers.</p><p> </p><p>Her Majesty’s Revenue and Customs have responsibility for investigating and enforcing compliance with the national minimum wage and the national living wage.</p>","Warrington South","David Mowat",,"2016-12-15T10:11:49.573Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657167/answer","Biography information for David Mowat","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657167/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657167/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-12-12","Social Services: Minimum Wage","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, pursuant to the Answer of 9 December 2016 to Question 56017, what comparative assessment he has made of care providers' compliance with the national minimum wage and the business failure of such providers.","false","Biography information for Paul Blomfield","Sheffield Central","Paul Blomfield","57257"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657168","Department of Health","false","2016-12-16","<p>The Department is currently involved in two cases of litigation related to people affected by infected National Health Service supplied blood or blood products. It would not be appropriate to comment further on these cases.</p>","Oxford West and Abingdon","Nicola Blackwood",,"2016-12-16T12:16:46.08Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657168/answer","Biography information for Baroness Blackwood of North Oxford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657168/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657168/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-12-12","Blood: Contamination","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many cases of litigation related to people affected by contaminated blood and the related support scheme his Department is involved in resolving.","false","Biography information for Diana Johnson","Kingston upon Hull North","Diana Johnson","57253"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657169","Department of Health","false","2016-12-19","<p>The Royal College of General Practitioners’ (GP) recommendation on how to learn this area of practice is by work placed learning in primary care where all trainees now have a minimum of 18 months experience. This is in addition to team work learning such as the toolkit specifically designed for primary care teams to evaluate the extent to which they and their practices promote mental health.</p><p> </p><p>Many GP training programmes contain placements of varying length in psychiatry units. These will give exposure to patients with mental health problems but it is important that as a GP specialty trainee they also gain a broader understanding of mental health than can be obtained in the psychiatry ward or clinics.</p><p> </p><p>Health Education England ensures that GP training is supplemented by courses in mental health and e-learning modules including innovative learning opportunities with other health professionals, including psychiatry trainees, with an emphasis on the importance of the team work required across health, social care and the third sector.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","57272","2016-12-19T16:38:14.177Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657169/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657169/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657169/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-12-12","General Practitioners: Mental Health Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what assessment he has made of the implications for his policies of the findings of Mind in its report, Better equipped, better care, published in November 2016, that 46 per cent of speciality trainee GPs in England and Wales gained practical experience of mental health services in 2015.","false","Biography information for Sir George Howarth","Knowsley","Mr George Howarth","57271"
