"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657190","Home Office","false","2017-04-20","<p>The Home Office has continued to increase the number of asylum Decision Makers and has ongoing recruitment campaigns, to cope with demand and to ensure we continue to meet our service standards. All asylum claims lodged in the UK are carefully considered on their individual merits against a background of relevant case law and up to date country information.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2017-04-20T17:13:14.683Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657190/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657190/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657190/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-12-12","Asylum","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what estimate she has made of the number of civil servants based in her Department who work full-time on asylum casework; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","57083"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657191","Home Office","false","2016-12-20","<p>There has been no cost of processing civil penalty appeals under the Right to Rent scheme as there have not been any appeals lodged since the start of the scheme on 1 December 2014.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2016-12-20T17:55:14.373Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657191/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657191/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657191/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-12-12","Undocumented Migrants: Private Rented Housing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what the total cost has been of processing civil penalty appeals under the right to rent provisions.","false","Biography information for Stuart C. McDonald","Cumbernauld, Kilsyth and Kirkintilloch East","Stuart C. McDonald","57103"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657192","Home Office","false","2017-01-11","<p>The opinion of the Home Office Chief Scientific Adviser, Professor Bernard Silverman FRS, was sought on the subject of dental age determination and I have placed a copy of his report in the Library.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2017-01-11T17:32:59.127Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657192/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657192/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657192/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-12-12","Asylum: Young People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, pursuant to the Answer of 29 November 2016 to Question 52848, whether it was her Department's chief scientific adviser or the Government's Chief Scientific Adviser who expressed concerns about the scientific basis of the trial; and if she will place in the Library or otherwise publish copies of any correspondence outlining those concerns.","false","Biography information for Ms Diane Abbott","Hackney North and Stoke Newington","Ms Diane Abbott","57161"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657193","Home Office","false","2017-01-31","<p>The information requested is not routinely collated in the format sought by the hon. Member. At the time of the Evaluation of Phase 1 of the scheme, volumes of data were low enough to allow manual analysis of individual cases. Volumes of data are now at a level which makes conducting such an exercise cost prohibitive.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2017-01-31T12:51:51.08Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657193/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657193/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657193/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-12-12","Undocumented Migrants: Private Rented Housing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many undocumented migrants identified through the right to rent scheme have since been (a) granted discretionary leave to remain, (b) granted refugee status, (c) granted humanitarian protection and (d) recognised as a victim of trafficking or modern day slavery.","false","Biography information for Stuart C. McDonald","Cumbernauld, Kilsyth and Kirkintilloch East","Stuart C. McDonald","57151"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657194","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2016-12-16","<p>There are around 22,000 youth teams across England. The vast majority rely, entirely or mainly, on volunteers to run these teams and the vast majority of these volunteers have nothing but the best interests of the children, and the game, at heart.</p><p> </p><p>All team officials, coaches, managers, welfare officers and referees are considered in regulated activity and have an enhanced check with the Disclosure and Barring Service 's children’s barred list. The Football Association completes around 55,000 checks every year on such regulated activity. All coaches, whether qualified or with an assistant status, are considered in regulated activity.</p>","Chatham and Aylesford","Tracey Crouch",,"2016-12-16T08:33:21.98Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657194/answer","Biography information for Tracey Crouch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657194/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657194/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-12-12","Football: Voluntary Work","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, if she will estimate the number of volunteers in the football industry who work unsupervised with children.","false","Biography information for Diana Johnson","Kingston upon Hull North","Diana Johnson","57150"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657195","Home Office","false","2016-12-20","<p>The information requested is available in the Home Office Annual Report and Accounts (ARA). The ARA is published on the gov.uk website and can be found via this link - https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/home-office-annual-report-and-accounts-2015-to-2016</p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton",,"2016-12-20T17:51:24.523Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657195/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657195/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657195/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-12-12","Home Office: Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what the percentage gap in earnings is between the highest-paid and lowest-paid full-time employee in her Department.","false","Biography information for Jake Berry","Rossendale and Darwen","Jake Berry","56990"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657196","Home Office","false","2016-12-19","<p>The police already have the power under section 59 of the Police Reform Act 2002 to seize vehicles, including off-road bikes and mopeds. This can be as a result of using a vehicle in a careless and inconsiderate manner, contrary to the Road Traffic Act 1988, and in a manner causing alarm, distress or annoyance to members of the public.</p><p>This enables the police to put an immediate stop to this dangerous and anti-social behaviour. How this power is used is an operational matter for the police.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2016-12-19T17:19:29.657Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657196/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657196/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657196/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-12-12","Motorcycles: Antisocial Behaviour","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, if she will review the powers available to the police to tackle anti-social use of off-road bikes and mopeds.","false","Biography information for Steve McCabe","Birmingham, Selly Oak","Steve McCabe","56963"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657197","Home Office","false","2017-04-20","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the oral statement on the Corporate Governance Green Paper of 29 November 2016, Official Report, Column 1408.</p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton",,"2017-04-20T07:10:51.107Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657197/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657197/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657197/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-12-12","Home Office: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what plans her Department has to include worker representation on its departmental board.","false","Biography information for Jake Berry","Rossendale and Darwen","Jake Berry","57012"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657198","Home Office","false","2017-01-10","<p>As at the 31st March 2016 the percentage gap in earnings between the highest paid and median full-time pay in the Home Office expressed as a percentage of the highest paid employee earnings is 83.1%.</p><p>The most recent data is published in theHome Office Annual Report (ARA) and can be found on the gov.uk website: https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/home-office-annual-report-and-accounts-2015-to-2016</p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton",,"2017-01-10T18:06:03.433Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657198/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657198/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657198/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-12-12","Home Office: Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what the percentage gap in earnings is between the pay of full-time staff in the highest pay grade in her Department and average full-time pay in that Department.","false","Biography information for Jake Berry","Rossendale and Darwen","Jake Berry","57034"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657199","Home Office","false","2016-12-20","<p>The current Home Office system does not centrally record the basis of an asylum claim. The data requested could only be provided at disproportionate cost by examination of individual case records. We aim to decide all straightforward asylum claims within 6 months, however there will be some claims which are more complex, including those who have suffered abhorrent acts such as torture. We aim to decide these cases within 12 months.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2016-12-20T17:13:24.793Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657199/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657199/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657199/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-12-12","Asylum","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what estimate she has made of the number of people who have suffered torture abroad and are awaiting her Department's decision on their claim for asylum; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","57045"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657200","Home Office","false","2016-12-19","<p>Tackling knife crime is a priority for the Government and we are taking firm action including warning young people about the dangers of carrying knives, and working with retailers to ensure there are effective controls on knife sales in the high street and online, and legislating to ban the sale and importation of zombie knives.</p><p>21 police forces, including the Metropolitan Police Service, also recently took part in a week of action against knife crime, which involved targeting habitual knife carriers, weapon sweeps, the use of surrender bins, and test purchases from identified retailers.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2016-12-19T18:26:16.207Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657200/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657200/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657200/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-12-12","Knives: Greater London","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what recent steps she has taken to reduce knife crime in London.","false","Biography information for Ms Harriet Harman","Camberwell and Peckham","Ms Harriet Harman","57070"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657201","Home Office","false","2016-12-19","<p>The Prime Minister has been clear that she wants to protect the status of EU nationals already living in the UK, and the only circumstances in which that wouldn’t be possible is if British citizens’ rights in other EU Member States were not protected in return.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2016-12-19T18:07:36.693Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657201/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657201/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657201/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-12-12","EU Nationals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what steps she is taking to protect the status of EU nationals living in the UK when the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Ms Harriet Harman","Camberwell and Peckham","Ms Harriet Harman","57072"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657202","Home Office","false","2016-12-23","<p>The DBS does not receive information from applicants that enables it to report statistics accurately on the total number of applications relating to specific employers, including the Football Association, unless they are a Registered Body.</p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton",,"2016-12-23T10:49:40.407Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657202/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657202/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657202/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-12-12","Vetting","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many applications for criminal records checks have been received by the Disclosure and Barring Service from the Football Association in each year since 2009-10; and what proportion of those applications (a) passed and (b) failed.","false","Biography information for Diana Johnson","Kingston upon Hull North","Diana Johnson","57048"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657203","Home Office","false","2016-12-20","<p>The current Home Office system does not centrally record the basis of an asylum claim. The data requested could only be provided at disproportionate cost by examination of individual case records.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2016-12-20T17:00:36.32Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657203/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657203/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657203/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-12-12","Asylum","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what estimate she has made of the number of people who have been granted asylum in the UK after being victims of torture abroad in each of the last six years; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","57054"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657204","Department for International Development","false","2016-12-15","<p>DFID’s <strong>Strategic Vision</strong> for Girls and Women, published in 2011, sets out four, interlinked game-changing ‘pillars’ critical for empowering girls and women:</p><p>1. Girls’ completion of primary and secondary education</p><p>2. Economic empowerment</p><p>3. Ability to live free from violence</p><p>4. Universal sexual and reproductive health and rights.</p><p>DFID is committed to delivering the Prime Minister’s promise on tackling modern slavery and the 2015 government manifesto. ‘We will promote girls’ education, encourage equal access to property rights and work to achieve access to family planning for everyone who wants it. We will continue to lead efforts to tackle violence against women and girls, end FGM and combat early and forced marriage, both at home and abroad’.</p>","Stockton South","James Wharton",,"2016-12-15T13:43:20.917Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657204/answer","Biography information for James Wharton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657204/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657204/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2016-12-12","Developing Countries: Females","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what her strategic objectives are in relation to women and girls in developing countries.","false","Biography information for Paula Sherriff","Dewsbury","Paula Sherriff","56961"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657205","Department for International Development","false","2016-12-19","<p>The Office for National Statistics publish the salary ratio of highest to median earners for each Civil Service organization. These ratios are published annually as part of Civil Service Statistics and can be found on the Office for National Statistics website at www.ons.gov.uk/employmentandlabourmarket/ peopleinwork/publicsectorpersonnel/bulletins/civilservicestatistics/2016</p>","Stockton South","James Wharton",,"2016-12-19T16:44:54.137Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657205/answer","Biography information for James Wharton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657205/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657205/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2016-12-12","Department for International Development: Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what the percentage gap in earnings is between the pay of full-time staff in the highest pay grade in her Department and average full-time pay in that Department.","false","Biography information for Jake Berry","Rossendale and Darwen","Jake Berry","57035"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657206","Department for International Development","false","2016-12-20","<p>I refer the Hon. Member to the oral statement on the Corporate Governance Green Paper of 29 November 2016, Official Report, Column 1408.</p>","Stockton South","James Wharton",,"2016-12-20T12:55:58.803Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657206/answer","Biography information for James Wharton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657206/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657206/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2016-12-12","Department for International Development: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what plans her Department has to include worker representation on its departmental board.","false","Biography information for Jake Berry","Rossendale and Darwen","Jake Berry","57013"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657207","Department for International Development","false","2016-12-19","<p>DFID does not publish details of the salary of their highest to lowest paid employees.</p><p>The Office for National Statistics do, however, publish the salary ratio of highest to median earners for each Civil Service organization. These ratios are published annually as part of Civil Service Statistics and can be found on the Office for National Statistics website at <a href="http://www.ons.gov.uk/%20employmentandlabourmarket/peopleinwork/publicsectorpersonnel/bulletins/civilservicestatistics/2016" target="_blank">www.ons.gov.uk/ employmentandlabourmarket/peopleinwork/publicsectorpersonnel/bulletins/civilservicestatistics/2016</a></p>","Stockton South","James Wharton",,"2016-12-19T16:44:04.107Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657207/answer","Biography information for James Wharton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657207/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657207/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2016-12-12","Department for International Development: Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what the percentage gap in earnings is between the highest-paid and lowest-paid full-time employee in her Department.","false","Biography information for Jake Berry","Rossendale and Darwen","Jake Berry","56991"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657208","Department for International Development","false","2016-12-20","<p>Mental health is a key priority for DFID and we are committed to supporting the health and wellbeing of our staff in line with commitments set out in both the Civil Service Talent Action Plan and the Health &amp; Wellbeing Strategic Action Plan. We support staff through a range of measures.</p><p>DFID is based across two sites in the UK – in England and Scotland. We support both the “Time to Change” campaign (in England) and SeeMe in Scotland to end the stigma associated with mental health and raise awareness through supporting Mental Health Awareness Week. We have also recently launched a series of products on personal and team resilience and we promote the Civil Service e-learning to expand staff and managers knowledge of mental health issues.</p><p>DFID’s Employee Assistance Programme (EAP) offers Telephone and Face to Face Counselling for all staff experiencing mental ill health across our global workforce. The service also provides a wide range of online information and advice on work/life issues.</p><p>DFID’s HR teams and Occupational Health Services provide support and advice for staff and managers to ensure a successful return to work after a period of mental ill health.</p><p>DFID also has a Listening Network, an informal peer staff network, to complement the help already available.</p><p> </p>","Stockton South","James Wharton",,"2016-12-20T12:59:04.767Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657208/answer","Biography information for James Wharton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657208/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657208/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2016-12-12","Department for International Development: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what measures her Department has in place to support those of its staff who have mental health problems.","false","Biography information for Helen Whately","Faversham and Mid Kent","Helen Whately","57128"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657209","Department for International Development","false","2016-12-20","<p>DFID is on track with our commitment to improve the nutrition of 50 million people by 2020. We are continuing to strengthen nutrition-specific programmes in the countries where we work. These services will contribute to reducing stunting and make sure acute malnutrition is treated effectively. We support Governments that are part of the Scaling up Nutrition (SUN) Movement to do the same.</p>","Stockton South","James Wharton",,"2016-12-20T12:56:30.547Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657209/answer","Biography information for James Wharton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657209/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657209/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2016-12-12","Developing Countries: Nutrition","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what progress has been made on plans to improve nutrition-specific programmes in low and middle-income countries.","false","Biography information for Brendan O'Hara","Argyll and Bute","Brendan O'Hara","57092"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657210","Department for International Development","false","2016-12-20","<p>The Secretary of State for International Development is a member of the Scaling up Nutrition (SUN) Lead Group. DFID funds the SUN Movement Secretariat, the SUN Civil Society Network and is providing assistance to Governments in the SUN Movement.</p>","Stockton South","James Wharton",,"2016-12-20T12:57:49.26Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657210/answer","Biography information for James Wharton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657210/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657210/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2016-12-12","Developing Countries: Nutrition","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what steps her Department is taking to support the Scaling Up Nutrition movement in its work on global malnutrition.","false","Biography information for Brendan O'Hara","Argyll and Bute","Brendan O'Hara","57094"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657211","Ministry of Justice","false","2016-12-15","<p>We shall set out our proposals for a Bill of Rights in due course, and we shall of course consult fully on those proposals.</p>","North East Hertfordshire","Sir Oliver Heald",,"2016-12-15T17:25:00.423Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657211/answer","Biography information for Sir Oliver Heald","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657211/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657211/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2016-12-12","Bill of Rights","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what the timetable is for the introduction of proposals for a British Bill of Rights.","false","Biography information for Ms Harriet Harman","Camberwell and Peckham","Ms Harriet Harman","56978"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657212","Ministry of Justice","false","2016-12-15","<p>The information requested is not held centrally.</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah",,"2016-12-15T17:31:32.42Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657212/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657212/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657212/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2016-12-12","Prisons: Civil Disorder","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, whether any member of the (a) National Tactical Response Group and (b) Tornado Team has been injured during a call-out in the last two years.","false","Biography information for Richard Burgon","Leeds East","Richard Burgon","57182"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657213","Ministry of Justice","false","2016-12-15","<p>I refer the Honourable Member to the answer given to PQ 22415 on 18 January 2016, and to PQ45566 on 16 September 2016.</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah",,"2016-12-15T17:38:00.557Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657213/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657213/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657213/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2016-12-12","Prisons: Civil Disorder","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, on how many occasions the (a) National Tactical Response Group and (b) Tornado Team have been called out to prisons in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Richard Burgon","Leeds East","Richard Burgon","57183"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657214","Ministry of Justice","false","2016-12-16","<p>NOMS’ national policies and procedures are reviewed regularly to ensure that they are effective in dealing with threats to prisons, including the importation of prohibited items.</p><p> </p><p>We are planning to boost our searching capability within prisons and are examining options for better equipped and more widely deployed searching teams at national, regional and local levels. We are also investing in improved intelligence capabilities at all levels to enable searching and other security activities to be targeted more effectively.</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah",,"2016-12-16T13:12:35.247Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657214/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657214/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657214/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2016-12-12","Prisons: Smuggling","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what assessment her Department has made of the effectiveness of searches of (a) prison staff and (b) visitors when entering prisons on reducing the number of prohibited items being brought into prisons.","false","Biography information for Jim McMahon","Oldham West and Royton","Jim McMahon","57129"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657215","Ministry of Justice","false","2016-12-20","<p>We take the issue of mobile phones in prisons very seriously and are committed to minimising the number of mobile phones entering prisons and to detecting and disrupting their use by prisoners when they are smuggled into prisons.</p><p> </p><p>With the help of leading mobile phone companies and cutting edge technology, we are stepping up measures to find and block mobile phones.</p><p> </p><p>The Secretary of State has recently signed a Memorandum of Understanding with Mobile Phone Network Operators to develop a system which prevents unauthorised mobile phone use within prisons.</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah",,"2016-12-20T17:36:17.563Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657215/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657215/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657215/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2016-12-12","Prisons: Mobile Phones","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what assessment her Department has made of the effectiveness of current controls of mobile telephones in prisons.","false","Biography information for Jim McMahon","Oldham West and Royton","Jim McMahon","57130"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657216","Ministry of Justice","false","2016-12-20","<p>The Ministry of Justice (MoJ) Wellbeing Strategy, launched in November 2015, sets out MoJ’s commitment to supporting the mental and physical wellbeing of all our staff.</p><p>Employees can find additional information and signposting to the support available on internal Wellbeing pages on the MoJ intranet, and can seek advice and peer support from the MoJ Disability Staff Networks. In addition our independent Employee Assistance Provision provides confidential counselling sessions for employees, 24 hour telephone support, coaching for managers, mediation and group counselling.</p>","Bracknell","Dr Phillip Lee",,"2016-12-20T17:48:48.383Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657216/answer","Biography information for Dr Phillip Lee","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657216/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657216/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2016-12-12","Ministry of Justice: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what measures her Department has in place to support those of its staff who have mental health problems.","false","Biography information for Helen Whately","Faversham and Mid Kent","Helen Whately","57124"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657217","Ministry of Justice","false","2016-12-22","<p>It is not our practice to publish ministerial correspondence.</p><p>The Ministry of Justice has a note of the meeting of 22 February 2016 when the then Justice Secretary met the Honourable Member and your constituent Tina Trowhill to discuss baby ashes and cremation practices. A civil servant attended the meeting.</p><p>The Government has made clear that historic infant cremation practices must never be repeated. That is why we took decisive action, following a well-received consultation, to introduce a statutory definition of ashes and modernise crematoria processes. Other work is in hand.</p><p>Hull City Council has decided against a local investigation, and has made substantial improvements to cremation processes.</p>","Bracknell","Dr Phillip Lee","57202 ; 57203","2016-12-22T01:57:33.927Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657217/answer","Biography information for Dr Phillip Lee","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657217/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657217/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2016-12-12","Cremation: Babies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, if her Department will publish all correspondence her and her predecessor had with (a) Hull City Council, (b) the hon. Member for Kingston upon Hull North and (c) constituent Tina Trowhill on baby ashes and cremation working practices.","false","Biography information for Diana Johnson","Kingston upon Hull North","Diana Johnson","57201"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657219","Ministry of Justice","false","2016-12-20","<p>We must ensure legal aid is sustainable and fair - both for those who need it and the taxpayer who pays for it. That is why we have made sure support remains available to the most vulnerable and in the most serious cases.</p><p>The table below shows the total number of legal aid applications received by the Legal Aid Agency (LAA) alongside those not granted legal aid in the Wansbeck constituency. This information is based upon applications made to legal aid providers located and offering services within the Wansbeck constituency. Figures for those applications not granted include both those refused as well as those rejected due to incomplete information (which may then be granted in any subsequent application).</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p>Number of applications received</p></td><td><p>Number of applications not granted</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013-2014</p></td><td><p>741</p></td><td><p>71</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014-2015</p></td><td><p>671</p></td><td><p>33</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2015-2016</p></td><td><p>614</p></td><td><p>34</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p>These figures reflect applications made via the criminal courts, civil representation and exceptional case funding schemes only. Data are not held for the legal aid schemes covering Legal Help and pre-charge criminal advice<em>.</em></p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah",,"2016-12-20T17:52:26.497Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657219/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657219/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657219/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2016-12-12","Legal Aid Scheme: Wansbeck","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many people attempted to access legal aid and were declined in Wansbeck constituency in the last three years.","false","Biography information for Ian Lavery","Wansbeck","Ian Lavery","57191"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657220","Ministry of Justice","false","2016-12-20","<p>The Office for National Statistics publish the salary ratio of highest to median earners for each Civil Service organization. These ratios are published annually as part of Civil Service Statistics and can be found on the Office for National Statistics website:</p><p><a href="https://www.ons.gov.uk/employmentandlabourmarket/peopleinwork/publicsectorpersonnel/bulletins/civilservicestatistics/2016" target="_blank">https://www.ons.gov.uk/employmentandlabourmarket/peopleinwork/publicsectorpersonnel/bulletins/civilservicestatistics/2016</a></p>","Bracknell","Dr Phillip Lee","57037","2016-12-20T17:57:04.957Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657220/answer","Biography information for Dr Phillip Lee","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657220/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657220/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2016-12-12","Ministry of Justice: Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what the percentage gap in earnings is between the highest-paid and lowest-paid full-time employee in her Department.","false","Biography information for Jake Berry","Rossendale and Darwen","Jake Berry","56993"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657221","Ministry of Justice","true","2016-12-15","<p>We want our prisons to be places of safety and reform, and so it is right that offenders who break prison rules are properly punished. Where this amounts to a criminal offence, prisoners should expect to be investigated by the police and face more serious sanctions.</p><p>We are committed to improving safety across the prison estate and are already taking action. This includes tackling the use of drugs, mobile phones and drones, while recruiting new staff and improving protection for staff.</p><p>Information on the number of additional days awarded to prisoners as a result of adjudications for assaults against staff and prisoners in each of the last five years can be found in the attached table.</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah",,"2016-12-15T17:43:03.253Z","2017-02-07T13:57:50.317Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657221/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657221/answer","56955 - table.xlsx","assaults against staff & prisoners - adjudications","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657221/answer","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657221/answer/previousversion/26782","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","54","Justice","Justice","2016-12-12","Prisoners: Crimes of Violence","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many extra days imprisonment have been given to prisoners for assaults committed on (a) fellow prisoners and (b) prison staff in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Richard Burgon","Leeds East","Richard Burgon","56955"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657222","Ministry of Justice","false","2016-12-15","<p>I refer the Honourable Member to the answer given to PQ 24706 on 10 February 2016.</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah",,"2016-12-15T17:36:12.32Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657222/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657222/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657222/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2016-12-12","Prisons: Weapons","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many weapons have been confiscated in prisons in each year since 2010; and what (a) number and (b) proportion of such weapons were firearms.","false","Biography information for Richard Burgon","Leeds East","Richard Burgon","56956"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657223","Ministry of Justice","false","2016-12-15","<p>The information requested is available on gov.uk.</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah",,"2016-12-15T17:34:18.02Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657223/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657223/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657223/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2016-12-12","Prison Accommodation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many people in each prison in England and Wales have been accommodated in cells designed for (a) one person but occupied by two and (b) two people but occupied by three in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Richard Burgon","Leeds East","Richard Burgon","56954"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657224","Ministry of Justice","false","2016-12-22","<p>The MoJ Board membership is in the line with guidance issued from the Cabinet Office, which outlines that Departmental Boards should, as a minimum, include Non-Executive Board Members, Ministers and Senior Civil Servants (including the Permanent Secretary).</p><p>In order to make Board discussions and meetings as effective as possible, a range of additional attendees may be invited on occasion to ensure robust scrutiny and a wider range advice is considered.</p><p>The membership will be guided by the Cabinet Office in order to keep a consistent approach with the rest of the departments.</p>","Bracknell","Dr Phillip Lee",,"2016-12-22T02:01:00.84Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657224/answer","Biography information for Dr Phillip Lee","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657224/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657224/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2016-12-12","Ministry of Justice: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what plans her Department has to include worker representation on its departmental board.","false","Biography information for Jake Berry","Rossendale and Darwen","Jake Berry","57015"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657225","Ministry of Justice","false","2016-12-20","<p>The Office for National Statistics publish the salary ratio of highest to median earners for each Civil Service organization. These ratios are published annually as part of Civil Service Statistics and can be found on the Office for National Statistics website:</p><p><a href="https://www.ons.gov.uk/employmentandlabourmarket/peopleinwork/publicsectorpersonnel/bulletins/civilservicestatistics/2016" target="_blank">https://www.ons.gov.uk/employmentandlabourmarket/peopleinwork/publicsectorpersonnel/bulletins/civilservicestatistics/2016</a></p>","Bracknell","Dr Phillip Lee","56993","2016-12-20T17:57:05.037Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657225/answer","Biography information for Dr Phillip Lee","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657225/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657225/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2016-12-12","Ministry of Justice: Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what the percentage gap in earnings is between the pay of full-time staff in the highest pay grade in her Department and average full-time pay in that Department.","false","Biography information for Jake Berry","Rossendale and Darwen","Jake Berry","57037"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657226","Ministry of Justice","false","2016-12-23","<p>It is hugely important that we pardon people convicted of historical sexual offences who would be innocent of any crime today. Through pardons and the existing disregard process we will meet our manifesto commitment and put right these wrongs. Everyone living who obtains a pardon through the new process will also have obtained a disregard, meaning that they will be treated as if they had never committed the offence.</p><p> </p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah",,"2016-12-23T18:07:18.7Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657226/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657226/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657226/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2016-12-12","Homosexuality","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, if she will make an assessment of the potential merits of exonerating rather than pardoning gay and bisexual men convicted of now-abolished sexual offences; and if she will bring forward legislative proposals to exonerate gay and bisexual men of such offences.","false","Biography information for Diana Johnson","Kingston upon Hull North","Diana Johnson","57047"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657228","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-03-15","<p>The total cost of public interest transfers that have been approved within NOMS since January 2012 is £13.14m. The majority of these costs have been authorised to support staff transferring from prisons that have closed since 2012. Our records do not allow us to provide the breakdown by grade of staff in responding to your question</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah",,"2017-03-15T11:18:28.687Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657228/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657228/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657228/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2016-12-12","National Offender Management Service: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many public interest transfers for each grade of staff have been approved within NOMS since January 2012; and what the cost was of those transfers.","false","Biography information for Yasmin Qureshi","Bolton South East","Yasmin Qureshi","57234"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657229","Ministry of Justice","false","2016-12-20","<p>Learning from the experience of previously opening new prisons, in order to support the opening of HM Prison Berwyn in North Wales experience from previously opening new prisons means that there is a need for Berwyn to be staffed by a balance of new and experienced staff. To facilitate the relocation of experienced staff to move to Berwyn, a bespoke relocation package was offered and capped at £22,000 which covered the total cost of a move of home or assisted travel to the vicinity of the new prison.</p><p> </p><p>For 2015 and 2016 (to date) the cost of public interest transfers to HM Prison Berwyn is £200,484. This relates to 25 employees.</p><p> </p><p>Information on the grades of these staff is not available.</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah",,"2016-12-20T17:36:10.557Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657229/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657229/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657229/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2016-12-12","National Offender Management Service: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what the total cost has been of capped public interest transfers to HM Prison Berwyn; and how many staff of each grade have been involved in such moves.","false","Biography information for Yasmin Qureshi","Bolton South East","Yasmin Qureshi","57235"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657230","Ministry of Justice","false","2016-12-15","<p>A range of methods to counter the threat posed by drones are being trialled and evaluated for their effectiveness across the prison estate. This includes the use of technology to detect and block drones, the enhancement of physical security and working with drone manufacturers.</p><p> </p><p>Information on netting fitted by each prison and by purpose is not held centrally and could only be obtained at disproportionate cost.</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah",,"2016-12-15T17:42:58.663Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657230/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657230/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657230/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2016-12-12","Prisons: Unmanned Air Vehicles","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many prisons in each category are (a) fitted and (b) not fitted with netting on outdoor areas to restrict drone access; and what other anti-drone techniques are being trialled in prisons.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","57249"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657231","Ministry of Justice","false","2016-12-22","<p>It is not our practice to publish ministerial correspondence.</p><p>The Ministry of Justice has a note of the meeting of 22 February 2016 when the then Justice Secretary met the Honourable Member and your constituent Tina Trowhill to discuss baby ashes and cremation practices. A civil servant attended the meeting.</p><p>The Government has made clear that historic infant cremation practices must never be repeated. That is why we took decisive action, following a well-received consultation, to introduce a statutory definition of ashes and modernise crematoria processes. Other work is in hand.</p><p>Hull City Council has decided against a local investigation, and has made substantial improvements to cremation processes.</p>","Bracknell","Dr Phillip Lee","57201 ; 57203","2016-12-22T01:57:34.003Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657231/answer","Biography information for Dr Phillip Lee","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657231/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657231/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2016-12-12","Cremation: Babies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, whether her Department holds a record of the meeting held by the then Secretary of State for Justice with the hon. Member for Kingston upon Hull North and constituent Tina Trowhill on 22 February 2016 on baby ashes and cremation working practices.","false","Biography information for Diana Johnson","Kingston upon Hull North","Diana Johnson","57202"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657232","Ministry of Justice","false","2016-12-22","<p>It is not our practice to publish ministerial correspondence.</p><p>The Ministry of Justice has a note of the meeting of 22 February 2016 when the then Justice Secretary met the Honourable Member and your constituent Tina Trowhill to discuss baby ashes and cremation practices. A civil servant attended the meeting.</p><p>The Government has made clear that historic infant cremation practices must never be repeated. That is why we took decisive action, following a well-received consultation, to introduce a statutory definition of ashes and modernise crematoria processes. Other work is in hand.</p><p>Hull City Council has decided against a local investigation, and has made substantial improvements to cremation processes.</p>","Bracknell","Dr Phillip Lee","57201 ; 57202","2016-12-22T01:57:34.067Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657232/answer","Biography information for Dr Phillip Lee","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657232/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657232/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2016-12-12","Cremation: Babies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, whether a civil servant was in attendance at the meeting held by the then Secretary of State for Justice with the hon. Member for Kingston upon Hull North and constituent Tina Trowhill on 22 February 2016 on baby ashes and cremation working practices.","false","Biography information for Diana Johnson","Kingston upon Hull North","Diana Johnson","57203"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657234","Northern Ireland Office","false","2016-12-19","<p>The UK Government’s relationship with the Irish Government has never been stronger. I regularly meet counterparts in the Irish Government and will continue to do so as we prepare for the UK’s exit from the EU.</p><p> </p><p>The Government is committed to preserving the current reciprocal status of Irish citizens within the United Kingdom, including in Northern Ireland, as originally provided for in the Ireland Act 1949 and in subsequent legislation.</p><p> </p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2016-12-19T13:07:01.217Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657234/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657234/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657234/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2016-12-12","Brexit: Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, what discussions his Department has had with the Irish government on the rights of Irish citizens in Northern Ireland after the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Tom Brake","Carshalton and Wallington","Tom Brake","57282"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657235","Northern Ireland Office","false","2016-12-20","<p>The Office for National Statistics publish the salary ratio of highest to median earners for each Civil Service organization. These ratios are published annually as part of Civil Service Statistics and can be found on the Office for National Statistics website:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.ons.gov.uk/employmentandlabourmarket/peopleinwork/publicsectorpersonnel/bulletins/civilservicestatistics/2016" target="_blank">https://www.ons.gov.uk/employmentandlabourmarket/peopleinwork/publicsectorpersonnel/bulletins/civilservicestatistics/2016</a></p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2016-12-20T12:35:32.76Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657235/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657235/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657235/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2016-12-12","Northern Ireland Office: Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, what the percentage gap in earnings is between the pay of full-time staff in the highest pay grade in his Department and average full-time pay in that Department.","false","Biography information for Jake Berry","Rossendale and Darwen","Jake Berry","57038"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657236","Northern Ireland Office","false","2016-12-21","<p>I refer the hon Member to the oral statement on the Corporate Governance Green Paper of 29 November 2016, Official Report, Column 1408.</p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2016-12-21T12:52:32.57Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657236/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657236/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657236/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2016-12-12","Northern Ireland Office: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, what plans his Department has to include worker representation on its departmental board.","false","Biography information for Jake Berry","Rossendale and Darwen","Jake Berry","57016"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657237","Northern Ireland Office","false","2016-12-20","<p>Government departments do not publish details of the salary of their highest to lowest paid employees.</p><p> </p><p>The Office for National Statistics do, however, publish the salary ratio of highest to median earners for each Civil Service organization. These ratios are published annually as part of Civil Service Statistics and can be found on the Office for National Statistics website:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.ons.gov.uk/employmentandlabourmarket/peopleinwork/publicsectorpersonnel/bulletins/civilservicestatistics/2016" target="_blank">https://www.ons.gov.uk/employmentandlabourmarket/peopleinwork/publicsectorpersonnel/bulletins/civilservicestatistics/2016</a></p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2016-12-20T12:36:57.083Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657237/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657237/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657237/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2016-12-12","Northern Ireland Office: Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, what the percentage gap in earnings is between the highest-paid and lowest-paid full-time employee in his Department.","false","Biography information for Jake Berry","Rossendale and Darwen","Jake Berry","56994"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657238","Northern Ireland Office","false","2016-12-16","<p>The Northern Ireland Office is able to access a number of services, including welfare support and employee assistance programmes, through our links with the Ministry of Justice. Specific support for staff who have mental health issues include:</p><p> </p><ul><li>An independent Employee Assistance Provision that provides confidential counselling sessions for employees, 24 hour telephone support, coaching for managers, mediation and group counselling;</li><li>Access to an internet Wellbeing Zone which contains wellbeing advice, fact sheets and videos on managing stress, healthy eating and healthy lifestyle choices. This is also part of our Employee Assistance Provision;</li><li>An Occupational Health provider that offers medical advice for managers supporting employees with mental health issues;</li><li>An attendance management system that is aligned with our wellbeing strategy and encourages proactive interventions for employees with mental health issues including prompt Occupational Health referrals with a view to ensuring that supportive measures and reasonable adjustments are identified and implemented promptly;</li><li>An individual Stress Assessment process; and</li><li>Toolkits for managers which recognise the links between musculoskeletal illnesses and mental health conditions.</li></ul>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2016-12-16T11:16:31.787Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657238/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657238/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657238/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2016-12-12","Northern Ireland Office: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, what measures his Department has in place to support those of its staff who have mental health problems.","false","Biography information for Helen Whately","Faversham and Mid Kent","Helen Whately","57137"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657239","Northern Ireland Office","false","2016-12-19","<p>There is a strong will to preserve the Common Travel Area. The UK Government, the Northern Ireland Executive and the Irish Government have been unequivocal – all want to maintain the current arrangements and avoid the introduction of physical border controls within the CTA.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2016-12-19T13:07:54.64Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657239/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657239/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657239/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2016-12-12","Common Travel Area","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, what his policy is on maintaining the Common Travel Area border between the UK and the Republic of Ireland following the UK leaving the EU; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Chris Leslie","Nottingham East","Chris Leslie","57207"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657240","Cabinet Office","false","2016-12-16","<p>The Prime Minister’s Office is an integral part of the Cabinet Office and is included in this reply.</p><p>Government departments do not publish details of the salary of their highest to lowest paid employees.</p><p>The Office for National Statistics do, however, publish the salary ratio of highest to median earners for each Civil Service organization. These ratios are published annually as part of Civil Service Statistics and can be found on the Office for National Statistics website:</p><p><a href="https://www.ons.gov.uk/employmentandlabourmarket/peopleinwork/publicsectorpersonnel/bulletins/civilservicestatistics/2016" target="_blank">https://www.ons.gov.uk/employmentandlabourmarket/peopleinwork/publicsectorpersonnel/bulletins/civilservicestatistics/2016</a></p>","Ipswich","Ben Gummer","56981 ; 57025 ; 57039","2016-12-16T12:03:16.847Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657240/answer","Biography information for Ben Gummer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657240/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657240/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-12-12","Cabinet Office: Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what the percentage gap in earnings is between the highest-paid and lowest-paid full-time employee in 10 Downing Street.","false","Biography information for Jake Berry","Rossendale and Darwen","Jake Berry","56995"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657241","Cabinet Office","false","2016-12-16","<p>I refer the Hon. Member to the oral statement on the Corporate Governance Green Paper of 29 November 2016, Official Report, Column 1408.</p>","Ipswich","Ben Gummer","57003","2016-12-16T12:05:44.95Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657241/answer","Biography information for Ben Gummer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657241/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657241/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-12-12","Prime Minister: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what plans 10 Downing Street has to include worker representation on its departmental board.","false","Biography information for Jake Berry","Rossendale and Darwen","Jake Berry","57017"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657242","Cabinet Office","false","2016-12-16","<p>The Prime Minister’s Office is an integral part of the Cabinet Office and is included in this reply.</p><p>Government departments do not publish details of the salary of their highest to lowest paid employees.</p><p>The Office for National Statistics do, however, publish the salary ratio of highest to median earners for each Civil Service organization. These ratios are published annually as part of Civil Service Statistics and can be found on the Office for National Statistics website:</p><p><a href="https://www.ons.gov.uk/employmentandlabourmarket/peopleinwork/publicsectorpersonnel/bulletins/civilservicestatistics/2016" target="_blank">https://www.ons.gov.uk/employmentandlabourmarket/peopleinwork/publicsectorpersonnel/bulletins/civilservicestatistics/2016</a></p>","Ipswich","Ben Gummer","56981 ; 56995 ; 57025","2016-12-16T12:03:16.97Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657242/answer","Biography information for Ben Gummer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657242/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657242/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-12-12","Cabinet Office: Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what the percentage gap in earnings is between the pay of full-time staff in the highest pay grade in 10 Downing Street and average full-time pay in that Department.","false","Biography information for Jake Berry","Rossendale and Darwen","Jake Berry","57039"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657243","Scotland Office","false","2016-12-19","<p>The Scotland Office does not employ staff directly. Matters relating to the terms and conditions of service of staff, including pay and gender pay gap analysis, are matters for the employing bodies.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2016-12-19T15:11:09.107Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657243/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657243/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657243/answer",,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2016-12-12","Scotland Office: Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, what the percentage gap in earnings is between the pay of full-time staff in the highest pay grade in his Department and average full-time pay in that Department.","false","Biography information for Jake Berry","Rossendale and Darwen","Jake Berry","57040"
