"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657246","Scotland Office","false","2016-12-15","<p>Following the Government’s review of the BBC Royal Charter, for the first time the new Framework Agreement places a formal commitment on the BBC to support Gaelic language services and to support MG ALBA in its work. The BBC and MG ALBA are currently discussing how this commitment will be implemented during the lifetime of the next Charter.</p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2016-12-15T13:11:30.857Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657246/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657246/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657246/answer",,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2016-12-12","Television: Scots Gaelic Language","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, what steps are being taken to secure the future of Gaelic broadcasting; and what discussions he plans to have with the BBC in ensuring the new BBC Charter delivers additional new programme investment into Gaelic television.","false","Biography information for Ian Murray","Edinburgh South","Ian Murray","57238"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657247","Department for Transport","false","2016-12-19","<p>The consultation on proposed changes to roadworthiness testing for vehicles of historical interest closed on 2 November. Over 2,000 responses were received. These are receiving consideration. We will be finalising the changes, including publishing our response, in the Spring of 2017.</p>","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes",,"2016-12-19T10:43:09.5Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657247/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657247/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657247/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-12-12","Motor Vehicles: Safety","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, when he plans to announce his final decision on implementing changes to the exemption from compulsory annual roadworthiness testing for vehicles of historic interest; and if he will make a statement.","true","Biography information for Sir Greg Knight","East Yorkshire","Sir Greg Knight","57251"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657248","Department for Transport","false","2016-12-16","<p>On Monday 28 November the Secretary of State for Transport announced further details of the additional funding announced in the 2016 Autumn Statement. The roads funding package document sets out the further roads funding that the government is committed to delivering in this Parliament and includes a full breakdown by local authority of the 2017/18 allocations of the Pothole Action Fund.</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/the-roads-funding-package" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/the-roads-funding-package</a></p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2016-12-16T11:17:32.393Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657248/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657248/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657248/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-12-12","Roads: Repairs and Maintenance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, pursuant to the Answer of 8 December 2016 to Question 56154, which local authorities have received funding allocated in the Autumn Statement 2016 from the Pothole Action Fund; and how much each such local authority has received.","false","Biography information for Diana Johnson","Kingston upon Hull North","Diana Johnson","57163"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657249","Department for Transport","false","2016-12-15","<p>The government has announced a multi-million pound compensation payment for at least 84,000 Southern passengers, to recognise the particular hardship of those who have suffered long delays, cancellations and disruption in recent months. Those who qualify will receive a payment equal to one month’s travel.</p><p><br>This payment is in addition to the compensation scheme ‘Delay Repay 15’, under which GTR passengers will be able to claim back 25% of the cost of the single fare for delays between 15 and 29 minutes, with passengers able to apply for compensation through the train operating company.</p><p> </p><p>The government has also committed to capping regulated rail fare increases at RPI+0% for the term of this Parliament from 2016 to 2020. This extends the cap on rail fares put in place for 2014 and 2015. This will benefit over a quarter of a million annual season ticket holders, providing an average saving to season ticket holders of £425 in the five years to 2020.</p>","Blackpool North and Cleveleys","Paul Maynard",,"2016-12-15T14:37:19.897Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657249/answer","Biography information for Paul Maynard","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657249/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657249/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-12-12","Southern","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, if he will introduce a formula to reduce rail ticket prices across the strike-affected southern region until normal service is resumed.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","57223"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657250","HM Treasury","false","2016-12-15","<p>The UK Government will guarantee funding for EU structural and investment projects in Wales, including European Regional Development projects, which are signed before we leave the EU. It will be for the Welsh Government to make an assessment of which projects should be pursued in areas of its competence within its Multiannual Financial Framework allocations in this period, and this guarantee will apply to any such projects.</p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2016-12-15T14:58:56.537Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657250/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657250/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657250/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-12-12","Public Transport: South Wales","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, whether any funding shortfall for the South Wales Metro resulting from the UK leaving the EU will be made up by the Government.","false","Biography information for Jessica Morden","Newport East","Jessica Morden","57224"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657251","Department for Transport","false","2016-12-15","<p>The Department has provided Volkswagen with the account details to make this payment and I expect to receive it very shortly.</p>","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes",,"2016-12-15T14:10:57.957Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657251/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657251/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657251/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-12-12","Volkswagen","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, pursuant to the Answer of 12 December 2016 to Question 56574, on Volkswagen, whether that payment will be made by 25 December 2016.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","57292"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657252","Department for Transport","false","2016-12-20","<p>Information on the gap in earnings between the highest and lowest paid full time employee can be found in the Remuneration and Staff Report section of the 2015/16 Department for Transport Annual Report and Accounts, which can be found here: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/dft-annual-reports-and-accounts" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/dft-annual-reports-and-accounts</a>.</p>","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes",,"2016-12-20T13:37:07.637Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657252/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657252/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657252/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-12-12","Department for Transport: Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what the percentage gap in earnings is between the highest-paid and lowest-paid full-time employee in his Department.","false","Biography information for Jake Berry","Rossendale and Darwen","Jake Berry","56997"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657254","Department for Transport","false","2016-12-20","<p>I refer the Hon. Member to the oral statement on Corporate Governance of 29 November 2016, Official Report, Column 1408, and to the associated green paper itself which can be found at:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/573438/beis-16-56-corporate-governance-reform-green-paper-final.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/573438/beis-16-56-corporate-governance-reform-green-paper-final.pdf</a></p><p> </p>","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes",,"2016-12-20T13:41:08.713Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657254/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657254/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657254/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-12-12","Department for Transport: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what plans his Department has to include worker representation on its departmental board.","false","Biography information for Jake Berry","Rossendale and Darwen","Jake Berry","57019"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657255","Department for Transport","false","2016-12-20","<p>The percentage gap between full-time staff in the highest pay grade and average full-time pay in the Department (including the Executive Agencies) is 84%.</p>","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes",,"2016-12-20T13:44:08.72Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657255/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657255/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657255/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-12-12","Department for Transport: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what the percentage gap in earnings is between the pay of full-time staff in the highest pay grade in his Department and average full-time pay in that Department.","false","Biography information for Jake Berry","Rossendale and Darwen","Jake Berry","57041"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657256","Department for Transport","false","2016-12-20","<p>The unnecessary industrial action is clearly having an effect on both passengers and businesses.</p><p> </p><p>I am in regular contact with Govia Thameslink Railway and any retailer who feels that the disruption has had a detrimental effect on their business, should contact their managing Agent, Amey PT. Govia has assured me that each case will be looked at on an individual basis.</p>","Blackpool North and Cleveleys","Paul Maynard",,"2016-12-20T11:30:50.597Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657256/answer","Biography information for Paul Maynard","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657256/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657256/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-12-12","Southern","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, if he will hold discussions with Govia Thameslink Railway on the action it might take to mitigate the financial effect on retail outlets in train stations of industrial action by employees of Southern Rail.","false","Biography information for Jeremy Quin","Horsham","Jeremy Quin","56968"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657257","Department for Transport","false","2016-12-15","<p>The coach market in the UK is deregulated, as is the bus market in GB outside London. It is for individual bus and coach companies to decide how to respond to the action by Southern Rail.</p><p> </p><p>However, my officials are closely liaising with the Confederation of Passenger Transport, the bus and coach trade body, to determine how bus and coach operators can best assist with providing alternative transport.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones","56947","2016-12-15T14:02:10.047Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657257/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657257/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657257/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-12-12","Southern: Industrial Disputes","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what discussions he has had with coach and bus companies on provision of alternative routes for commuters living in Worthing during industrial action on the Southern rail line.","false","Biography information for Tim Loughton","East Worthing and Shoreham","Tim Loughton","56944"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657258","Department for Transport","false","2016-12-15","<p>The coach market in the UK is deregulated, as is the bus market in GB outside London. It is for individual bus and coach companies to decide how to respond to the action by Southern Rail.</p><p> </p><p>However, my officials are closely liaising with the Confederation of Passenger Transport, the bus and coach trade body, to determine how bus and coach operators can best assist with providing alternative transport.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones","56944","2016-12-15T14:02:10.127Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657258/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657258/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657258/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-12-12","Southern: Industrial Disputes","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what discussions he has had with coach and bus companies on mitigating the effects of industrial action on the Southern rail line.","false","Biography information for Tim Loughton","East Worthing and Shoreham","Tim Loughton","56947"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657259","Department for Transport","false","2016-12-20","<p>The Government supports the need for airspace modernisation. In October 2016, the Aviation Minister, Lord Ahmad discussed airspace matters with the Scottish Transport Minister and expects to have further discussions with representatives of the devolved administrations regarding airspace matters over the coming months.</p><p> </p><p>Ministers do meet representatives from the aviation industry regularly and the need for airspace modernisation is often on the agenda.</p><p> </p><p>The Government supports the need for airspace modernisation, but has not made a specific assessment of its environmental benefits.</p>","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes","56932 ; 57091","2016-12-20T13:54:22.32Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657259/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657259/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657259/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-12-12","Aviation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what recent discussions he has had with his counterparts in the devolved administrations on the modernisation of UK airspace.","false","Biography information for Drew Hendry","Inverness, Nairn, Badenoch and Strathspey","Drew Hendry","56931"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657260","Department for Transport","false","2016-12-20","<p>The Government supports the need for airspace modernisation. In October 2016, the Aviation Minister, Lord Ahmad discussed airspace matters with the Scottish Transport Minister and expects to have further discussions with representatives of the devolved administrations regarding airspace matters over the coming months.</p><p> </p><p>Ministers do meet representatives from the aviation industry regularly and the need for airspace modernisation is often on the agenda.</p><p> </p><p>The Government supports the need for airspace modernisation, but has not made a specific assessment of its environmental benefits.</p>","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes","56931 ; 57091","2016-12-20T13:54:22.38Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657260/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657260/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657260/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-12-12","Aviation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what recent discussions he has had with the aviation industry on the Government's agenda for airspace modernisation.","false","Biography information for Drew Hendry","Inverness, Nairn, Badenoch and Strathspey","Drew Hendry","56932"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657261","Department for Transport","false","2016-12-19","<p>We are currently delivering the largest railway modernisation programme for many years, including plans to electrify over 850 miles of track.</p><p> </p><p>We have continued ambition for the rail network and expect to continue our significant investment in the funding period. The exact level of this investment will be set out in the Statement of Funds Available.</p>","Blackpool North and Cleveleys","Paul Maynard",,"2016-12-19T14:57:03.247Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657261/answer","Biography information for Paul Maynard","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657261/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657261/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-12-12","Railways: Electrification","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how much from the public purse is allocated to rail electrification in each NUTS 1 region of the country in each of the next five years; and how many miles of track are to be electrified in each such region in each such year.","false","Biography information for Diana Johnson","Kingston upon Hull North","Diana Johnson","57210"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657262","Department for Transport","false","2016-12-20","<p>The Department for Transport (DfT) and its agencies take the mental wellbeing of its staff very seriously. DfT has a variety of policies and programmes designed to help staff that find themselves suffering with poor mental health.</p><p> </p><p>DfT has recently published an easy to access, practical guide for line managers on how they can support mental wellbeing in the workplace. It also includes advice on understanding the early warning signs and how to manage difficult conversations around mental health.</p><p> </p><p>DfT also supports workplace adjustment passports which are a living record of adjustments that a disabled member of staff requires, including staff with mental health problems. These documents are designed to do the following:</p><p>A) Ensure that both parties, the individual and the employer, have an accurate record of what has been agreed</p><p>B) Minimise the need to re-negotiate workplace adjustments every time the employee changes jobs, is re-located or assigned a new manager within the organisation</p><p>C) Provide employees and their line managers with the basis for discussions about workplace adjustments at future meetings.</p><p> </p><p>DfT has an Employee Assistance Programme (EAP). EAP support is tailored to the department and is provided by expert staff who understand our business. It offers support and signposts individuals to advice on things such as bereavement, depression, and anxiety. It also offers counselling sessions.</p><p>DfT has a Mental Health Buddy Network, set up by staff, for staff. It connects people who are suffering from mental health problems with another member of staff who is able to meet with them in complete confidence. The buddies are aware that they are not trained psychiatrists; they do not give advice but provide a listening ear, and signpost to the relevant, professional organisations.</p><p> </p><p>DfT has a dedicated mental health staff network, Time to Change, which is dedicated to changing the department’s culture, and remove the stigma surrounding mental health.</p>","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes",,"2016-12-20T14:04:52.6Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657262/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657262/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657262/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-12-12","Department for Transport: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what measures his Department has in place to support those of its staff who have mental health problems.","false","Biography information for Helen Whately","Faversham and Mid Kent","Helen Whately","57138"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657263","Department for Transport","false","2016-12-20","<p>My Department will publish information on the gender pay gap among employees in due course as outlined by the Regulations due to be laid in the Equality Act 2010.</p>","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes",,"2016-12-20T13:48:15.443Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657263/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657263/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657263/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-12-12","Department for Transport: Equal Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what plans his Department has to publish information on the gender pay gap among its employees.","false","Biography information for Jake Berry","Rossendale and Darwen","Jake Berry","57158"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657264","Department for Transport","false","2016-12-20","<p>The Government is committed to investing in the North East of England’s highways to improve and maintain roads up to 2020 through the following:</p><p> </p><ul><li>Highways Maintenance Block (2015/16 - 2020/21) = £268.0m.</li><li>Integrated Transport Block = £112.2m.</li><li>Two local major road schemes = £61.5m.</li><li>Significant funding to the Local Enterprise Partnerships, including £82.5m for the New Wear Crossing.</li><li>Highways England will be investing in major schemes as part of the Road Investment Strategy = £425m spend up to 2020, with several schemes continuing spend and construction beyond 2020.</li><li>Highways England will also undertake renewals and maintenance across the Strategic Road Network in Yorkshire and the North East up to 2020 = £600m.</li><li>Highways England will also spend in the region of £30m per annum on the routine maintenance of the Strategic Road Network in Yorkshire and the North East.</li></ul>","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes",,"2016-12-20T14:00:47.31Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657264/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657264/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657264/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-12-12","Roads: North East","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how much he plans to invest in the North East of England's highways to improve roads and to carry out essential maintenance up to 2020.","false","Biography information for Ian Lavery","Wansbeck","Ian Lavery","57194"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657265","Department for Transport","false","2016-12-20","<p>Govia Thameslink Railway is not required to provide the Department with detailed information on the causes of train failures. Officials have discussed camera failures with Southern, who confirmed that there has been a noticeable increase in camera defects reported. However, when investigated, no faults have been found by technical teams.</p>","Blackpool North and Cleveleys","Paul Maynard",,"2016-12-20T11:44:33.883Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657265/answer","Biography information for Paul Maynard","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657265/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657265/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-12-12","Southern","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what reports he has received on Southern trains (a) being taken out of service and (b) skipping stations or suffering delays due to cameras on driver-only operation trains failing.","false","Biography information for Jeremy Quin","Horsham","Jeremy Quin","56969"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657266","Department for Transport","false","2016-12-20","<p>The Government supports the need for airspace modernisation. In October 2016, the Aviation Minister, Lord Ahmad discussed airspace matters with the Scottish Transport Minister and expects to have further discussions with representatives of the devolved administrations regarding airspace matters over the coming months.</p><p> </p><p>Ministers do meet representatives from the aviation industry regularly and the need for airspace modernisation is often on the agenda.</p><p> </p><p>The Government supports the need for airspace modernisation, but has not made a specific assessment of its environmental benefits.</p>","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes","56931 ; 56932","2016-12-20T13:54:22.427Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657266/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657266/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657266/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-12-12","Aviation: Environment Protection","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what assessment his Department has made of the environmental benefits of modernising the UK's airspace.","false","Biography information for Drew Hendry","Inverness, Nairn, Badenoch and Strathspey","Drew Hendry","57091"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657267","Wales Office","false","2016-12-19","<p>Wales Office staff are generally employed on Ministry of Justice terms and conditions in respect of pay. The Ministry of Justice collect gender pay gap data and plans to publish information on the gender pay gap amongst its employees in line with legislation.</p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Aberconwy","Guto Bebb",,"2016-12-19T12:58:22.713Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657267/answer","Biography information for Guto Bebb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657267/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657267/answer",,,,,"28","Wales","Wales","2016-12-12","Wales Office: Equal Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Wales, what plans his Department has to publish information on the gender pay gap among its employees.","false","Biography information for Jake Berry","Rossendale and Darwen","Jake Berry","57159"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657268","Wales Office","false","2016-12-15","<p>The Department has not spent anything on Christmas functions specifically for hon. Members and Ministers; however hon. Members and Ministers may have attended Wales Office stakeholder functions.</p>","Aberconwy","Guto Bebb","56953","2016-12-15T17:33:28.417Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657268/answer","Biography information for Guto Bebb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657268/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657268/answer",,,,,"28","Wales","Wales","2016-12-12","Wales Office: Christmas","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Wales, how much his Department has spent on Christmas functions for hon. Members and Ministers in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Jo Stevens","Cardiff Central","Jo Stevens","56952"
