"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657270","Wales Office","false","2016-12-15","<p>There has been no spend on Christmas functions between 2012-15. The Department does not hold information for 2010 and 2011.</p>","Aberconwy","Guto Bebb",,"2016-12-15T17:35:17.627Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657270/answer","Biography information for Guto Bebb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657270/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657270/answer",,,,,"28","Wales","Wales","2016-12-12","Wales Office: Christmas","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Wales, how much his Department spent on Christmas functions in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Jo Stevens","Cardiff Central","Jo Stevens","56957"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657271","Wales Office","false","2016-12-15","<p>The Department has set a budget of £300 for Christmas functions in 2016.</p>","Aberconwy","Guto Bebb",,"2016-12-15T17:30:54.197Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657271/answer","Biography information for Guto Bebb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657271/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657271/answer",,,,,"28","Wales","Wales","2016-12-12","Wales Office: Christmas","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Wales, how much his Department plans to spend on Christmas functions in 2016.","false","Biography information for Jo Stevens","Cardiff Central","Jo Stevens","56958"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657272","Wales Office","false","2016-12-19","<p>I refer the hon Member to the oral statement on the Corporate Governance Green Paper of 29 November 2016, Official Report, Column 1408.</p>","Aberconwy","Guto Bebb",,"2016-12-19T12:59:36.957Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657272/answer","Biography information for Guto Bebb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657272/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657272/answer",,,,,"28","Wales","Wales","2016-12-12","Wales Office: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Wales, what plans his Department has to include worker representation on its departmental board.","false","Biography information for Jake Berry","Rossendale and Darwen","Jake Berry","57021"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657273","Wales Office","false","2016-12-19","<p>The Office for National Statistics publish the salary ratio of highest to median earners for each Civil Service organization. These ratios are published annually as part of Civil Service Statistics and can be found on the Office for National Statistics website:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.ons.gov.uk/employmentandlabourmarket/peopleinwork/publicsectorpersonnel/bulletins/civilservicestatistics/2016" target="_blank">https://www.ons.gov.uk/employmentandlabourmarket/peopleinwork/publicsectorpersonnel/bulletins/civilservicestatistics/2016</a></p><p> </p>","Aberconwy","Guto Bebb",,"2016-12-19T13:00:55.977Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657273/answer","Biography information for Guto Bebb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657273/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657273/answer",,,,,"28","Wales","Wales","2016-12-12","Wales Office: Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Wales, what the percentage gap in earnings is between the pay of full-time staff in the highest pay grade in his Department and average full-time pay in that Department.","false","Biography information for Jake Berry","Rossendale and Darwen","Jake Berry","57043"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657274","Wales Office","false","2016-12-19","<p>Government Departments do not publish details of the salary of their highest to lowest paid employees.</p><p> </p><p>The Office for National Statistics do, however, publish the salary ratio of highest to median earners for each Civil Service organization. These ratios are published annually as part of Civil Service Statistics and can be found on the Office for National Statistics website:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.ons.gov.uk/employmentandlabourmarket/peopleinwork/publicsectorpersonnel/bulletins/civilservicestatistics/2016" target="_blank">https://www.ons.gov.uk/employmentandlabourmarket/peopleinwork/publicsectorpersonnel/bulletins/civilservicestatistics/2016</a></p><p> </p><p> </p>","Aberconwy","Guto Bebb",,"2016-12-19T13:02:17.08Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657274/answer","Biography information for Guto Bebb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657274/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657274/answer",,,,,"28","Wales","Wales","2016-12-12","Wales Office: Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Wales, what the percentage gap in earnings is between the highest-paid and lowest-paid full-time employee in his Department.","false","Biography information for Jake Berry","Rossendale and Darwen","Jake Berry","56999"
